title: Partners In Research: Community Advisory Board (CAB) Interest Form
description:
Thank you for your interest in learning more about and potentially joining our community advisory board! 

Project ACHIEVE and Columbia Research Unit have been partners in research for over 20 years. Historically, the main focus of our efforts have been to speed the development of an HIV vaccine. In addition, we have conducted behavioral research among people with HIV. During the COVID-19 pandemic, research sites such as ours were mobilized and asked to participate in global COVID-19 vaccine clinical trials. Since then we have also conducted COVID vaccine and treatment research. Last but not least, we have been integral in addressing the Mpox outbreak by facilitating vaccine appointments and conducting qualitative and treatment research.

It is important that we involve diverse NYC residents to advise us on how to engage New Yorkers around the research we conduct, especially Black, Latinx, Asian/Pacific Islander, and Indigenous people from straight and LGBTQ+ communities. It is important that we hear voices and opinions from the ground about study protocols so we may conduct participatory-based research more effectively.

Please complete the following form and a staff person will reply with next steps which will include sending you a copy of our CAB Guidelines and potentially meeting other CAB members.
